Add esbuild build configs to SageMaker extensions

Since Code-OSS 1.116, extensions are compiled via esbuild during the
build pipeline. Extensions without an esbuild.mts config use the
fromLocalNormal path which only packages pre-existing files (via
vsce.listFiles). Since our extensions have out/** in .vscodeignore,
the compiled output was never included in the build artifact.

This adds esbuild.mts to each SageMaker extension so they are properly
compiled and bundled during the gulp build. The build system
automatically rewrites package.json main from ./out/extension to
./dist/extension for esbuild-bundled extensions.

Also adds typeRoots and types:["node"] to tsconfigs so tsgo type
checking passes.

